details.description: Deli St is an innovative concept aiming to offer healthy quick meal options for young professionals and neighborhood residents that are always on the go. In a hip neighborhood full of diverse eateries, breweries and coffee shops Deli St will draw the difference by baking their own goods, offering vegetarian and non-vegetarian options as well as a full coffee bar.

Vegan heaven it is. Soooo many options for ALL. It was our first time trying it and absolutely loved everything we ordered.
Their Vegan chocolate and carrot cake were amazing and so is Un Quickie and El Chingno(all vegan), excuse me if I’m spelling it wrong 😑 . Cute little cozy place and absolutely friendly staff. Must try.
I am a regular here for lunch, through original ownership and new. Hands down the best Torta in the city of Charlotte.

don’t let the unassuming exterior of the building fool you! deli st is fire! i got the st julien (italian) sub and it was absolutely fabulous. this cute lil’ deli carries a thoughtful assortment of accoutrements that includes a variety of vegan/veg/local offerings, wine and beer, the staff was super sweet, and the food was fresh and delicious. shop local!

Extremely disappointed in our visit today! We usually come here a few times a month and this time we were overcharged by quite a bit. The young lady stated their prices went up. Which I understand that prices increases but by $4 is ridiculous.  There are no prices on their menu and their online system states a total different price.

So it appears they are under new management and prices changed with new management as of the same day. This needs to be posted. This is extreme shady behavior and now they are blaming the clover system. Bad customer service!
Really good breakfast and lunch! Definitely worth the visit.

Looking for a breakfast that's both delicious and good for you?  Look no further than Deli St, a charming little spot that's quickly become my go-to for a healthy and satisfying morning meal.
From the moment you walk in, the bright and airy atmosphere sets the tone for a positive start to the day.  The décor is modern and clean, with pops of color and plenty of natural light.  It's a welcoming space, whether you're grabbing a quick bite on your way to work or settling in for a leisurely brunch with friends.
They offer a wide variety of options, catering to different dietary needs and preferences.  The staff is also incredibly friendly and knowledgeable, always happy to offer recommendations or answer questions about the menu.

Deli St. is a fantastic addition to the breakfast scene.  If you're looking for a healthy and delicious way to start your day, this is the place to be.  I highly recommend checking them out!  I give them a solid 5 out of 5 stars.
Cool place good coffee, friendly and helpful employee!
I love this place because it feels local and has great tasting food. Can be a bit pricey at times but it’s custom-made. Feels like a mom and pop deli from New York City.
Great vegan options.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Vegan, Beyond Wrap, Vegan Coconut Cake, Vegan Club

reviews_data.review_text: We visited on a Friday afternoon for lunch.  I got the Cindy Turkey and Jo got the avocado chicken salad.  This is place is very friendly.  Service is quick and the food is good.  Definitely recommend this place.
Good food 👍

Very disappointed with the young workers there.. I popped in at 3:15 … they close at 4…. They tell they can’t make my food bc they close their ktichen at 3:30 and I clearly have 15 minutes till they “close their kitchen” obviously they were lazy and did not want to work and get out of there. Won’t be giving my money to them anymore. Hopefully the owner/management can speak to their female employees about the hours of operations. Owner wasn’t present which is probably why the girls decided to make their own times up. Shame
One of my new favorite places!
Very original and vegan
I'm definitely coming back here, the sandwich was good and the watermelon juice on point. Good service
Amazing! They have just egg and beyond sausage
Yum!! This place is great! I had The Plaza torta, my friend had a smoothie both were outstanding!! The ambiance is nice and parking easy!
Great little brunch spot. Small interior but cozy with cool interior design. Small patio with a few tables. Very vegan friendly but plenty of standard items.
The customer service is always so friendly and they have so many vegan options!! The brownie and chocolate cake are insanely good and they have a full breakfast and lunch menu too.
The food is amazing, it's rarely too crowded, and it has a hard time getting boring. Amazing place to let the hours fly by with or without food.
Always fresh, friendly and delish. I always pick up at the drive thru, but it looks nice from outside too. Wish this review would let me add a photo of my sandwich...

Deli St has become my go to place for breakfast, lunch, and tacos! Their menu is extensive and vegan choices are plentiful. I have never tried anything I didn’t like here. The place is super cozy and nice with local art and cool plants. Outdoor and indoor seating so that you can enjoy our beautiful Charlotte weather when possible (almost all the time). The staff is super attentive and nice. They have a wide variety of drink options and their pastries are to die for!

I don’t often leave reviews, but I have to for Deli St.

The staff members were so kind, the menu is extensive, and everything we ordered was amazing. There’s ample parking, a drive-thru, well-shaded outdoor seating, and tons of vegan options.

We don’t live in Charlotte anymore, but if we did, this would be our go-to breakfast, lunch, and pastry spot.

Deli St is absolutely amazing. They don’t skimp on anything and it’s healthy (if you want fresh veggies and vegan options). Their vegan beyond wrap is a great deal (it’s so giant, don’t ever change!). Love love love! ♥️♥️♥️

When I first discovered this place I was delighted... but that changed quickly when I went to call in an order and the call kept dropping (or so I thought...) Still wanting a nice vegan breakfast I decided to walk in and place the order myself. I was curious about the phone issue so I called while waiting in line. The guy working the register answered it promptly... ok so I was getting hung up on. Not sure why but ok I'm here now might as well order.

I ordered the hottie in the morning (a vegan dish) and requested just egg as an extra and the vegan bacon. They gave me an actual omelet (yes I can tell the difference) and ACTUAL BACON. I've been vegan for over 10 years now. Why they would do this I have no clue. I was specific in what I asked for with the add-ons so I'm not sure why I received meat and eggs with this dish. This place is NOT VEGAN FRIENDLY AT ALL!!! VEGANS BEWARE THIS IS YOUR WARNING!!!

As a vegetarian this is by far my favorite breakfast place in Charlotte. Great people, quaint little area, and incredible food. From their breakfast sandwiches with egg, cheese, hash brown, and vegan sausage on their house Bolilo or the vegan buffalo chix sandwich with house ranch, as well as the great smoothies and coffee....this place rocks.

Vegetarians/Vegans in Charlotte, NC who have not had a chance to step in and have a bite in the cozy atmosphere with the great owner/staff are missing out big-time!

reviews_data.review_text: I just wanna take this time to say i love cindy and the staff at deli Street so much for the sexiest breakfast food in Charlotte.  Food so good it  will make you exchange a lambo in for a car battery. Food so good it will make you  stand in the DMV line for fun. Food so good you can stream  youtube videos on a pager. Food so good it make you call the cops for a crime that happend a year ago . All jokes aside, Its always a pleasure coming there in the morning and feeling so grateful to have vegan breakfast options 7 days out of the week. My favorite thing to get is the El chingon with just egg (vegan alternative egg) instead of the tofu. Its amazing.  I love you deli street!!!!!

Food is amazing. My husband I got three sandwiches and all of them were fantastic. I really like their habenero onions!

Chocolate cake was also delicious. Will definitely be back!

Maybe I ordered the wrong thing 😕 my girls seemed to enjoy their food and we all got something different ... I got a wrap with beyond beef veggies and just egg, but there was absolutely no flavor at all. I make this at home, and I quite enjoy it just wasn't seasoned enough of flavorful from the veggies. I love the taste of each type of vegetable 😋 and with a  crunch
Good food, quick, polite, friendly service

Stopped in for first-time visit on 11/20/23. Entry way has books to take/exchange. Nice! Outdoor seating in front under umbrellas. Surprising selections of beers and ales, lots of baked goods, breakfast all day and a full vegan menu. Coffees and baked goods are reasonably priced. I got a 12 oz mocha latte and a huge blueberry muffin for $7. Both were excellent. BTW, they also have a surprising selection of wines from around the world. I picked up 2 bottles of nice Italian wine to take to the fam for Thanksgiving. Friendly staff, warm vibes. Come visit this place; it's a happy little surprise. 😊
I've been coming here every Sunday before my kickball games (about 2 months) and this place never disappoints. Great service and food and way better than Common Market
Good variety of vegetarian and vegan options, plus good coffee and bakery treats

Breakfast sandwiches are on another level. Came to Charlotte for a 4-day vacation and ate here twice for breakfast.

My only con is that the coffee is a tad too hot when served, but I'm busy eating the sandwich while it cools down.

Today I had the pleasure of having lunch at Deli St and OMG I had the vegan BLT and the vegan quesadillas(this will be dinner).  Everything was seasoned well, hot and so much!! Customer service excellent!!  Definitely will be trying the vegan menu more!!  Thank you

A few people had recommended Deli Street and we were anxious to check it out.

We went there last week and it was wonderful!!  I can see why they spoke so highly of the place.

Ample parking, a fun entry with cute plaques about coffee & a lending library, interesting artwork (some for sale), a menu with lots of choices, super clean, friendly staff, and good vibes.

They have a vegan menu and a non-vegan menu so there is something for everyone!

They are very dog-friendly and have a nice outdoor seating area.

Most importantly, the food is fantastic!! We got sandwiches and hash browns, and desserts to go.  The vegan BLT on house bread was out of this world and the coconut cake was delectable and decadent (and I got 3 portions out of it), as was a huge cookie with nuts on it.  All homemade.

They are in the happening Plaza Midwood neighborhood, easy to get to, and even have a drive through.

Highly recommend and we'll definitely be back.
Every Vegan menu item from Deli St is so amazing. I order from here alll the time. The vegan torta is so delis!
I got the steak sandwhich it is amazing. Customer service is great and the food comes out quick and tastes amazing.
AMAZING food, great coffee/ espresso… nice staff and a very chill vibe
Always fresh deli meat, really like going here
The Food was great
Great food, great coffee, and great staff! Visiting for the day and glad I chose this spot for my breakfast.

Really nice atmosphere, really amazing food, and options for literally everyone!!!
I will be back
Food was great service was even better. I will definitely be coming back here on a regular.

It would be impossible for me to express how much I love Deli St but I’ll at least try!! Incredibly kind staff and owners, awesome beer selection, my favorite vegan breakfast in town (the hottie in the morning - add scrambled tofu), irresistible vegan baked goods, and more recently the best vegan tacos I’ve ever had in my life via their in-store pop up “Taco Vegano”. They even have a drive through window for pickup! I adore you Deli St!
Deli St. is the absolute BEST place for coffee, breakfast, or lunch in Charlotte! Incredible vegan options, awesome people, A+ service, and stellar vibe!! Would give em 10 stars if I could!!!
The best local spot in CLT for lunch. The bow tie pasta salad is incredible. They also have great deserts and dog treats. Give them a chance and you’ll be back.
Good deli thats very rare to find in charlotte.

Best cafe and vegan menu around Charlotte/plaza Midwood. Cindy & Enrique are always so nice. Many vegan options as well as regular menu (nonvegan). Lots of plants around the cafe for sale. Love coming here!
This place is in my top 2 and it’s not number 2 for lunch. One of the most underrated places in all of Charlotte. Service is excellent, food is fresh from breads to greens, can’t ask for much more.

The cashier was nice and the place has a great variety of drinks. However, the food lacks seasoning and flavor. I ordered the El Chingón (vegan)and the  and the tofu was not really seasoned.

I also ordered the vegan Beyond wrap. It was a decent size, but it is was not seasoned well. I feel like there should have been a sauce added to it. And for $12.99 it should have also included a side. But, there was no side.

I will probably give this place another try once they get a better sanitation grade. It was a 90 when I ordered today.

A little different than my usual. Food was very good, prices not out of line, but it would be helpful to have prices on the menu. I don't like having to ask for prices. Very clean, limited seating. I strongly recommend this place for breakfast sandwiches or lunch. My party of 3 enjoyed our food and the experience. We have a new favorite.
Great place for tasty smoothies and sandwiches!!!!
If you need a good breakfast sandwich, don’t waste another day not going here.  I’m sad it took us so long to check out this place!  So good and the portion of the hangover sandwich was MASSIVE!
I love the food and the people that works there, they have a lot of vegan options
Wonderful sandwiches and great service in a hip atmosphere. Definitely worth a visit!!

Deli St is a gem of the Plaza Midwood area. Great vegetarian and nonvegetarian options that are significantly better than any fast food you could get to-go. I tried the vegan club and would absolutely get it again.

Great place to eat with lots of vegan options! Very friendly staff and the owner is so sweet. Vegan breakfast options are the best! They also sell tacos on weekend evenings and WOW. The traditional tacos I've been craving for years. I could eat 40 of them. Cindy is so nice and always makes us feel like family.
I really enjoyed the vegan breakfast sandwiches here. It was awesome to meet Jam & learn about his art. Overall great vibe.
Cute place, good coffee
We got wraps and they were so delicious, not that bad on price and would for sure make it a go to spot for lunch
Deli street for life 🧡

not only is this little shop so cute but the food is phenomenal! i have been twice and each time i absolutely loved my sandwiches. they also have little dog treats by the register so i always grab two and my dogs love them! they have a bakery i have yet to try but i always find myself staring at all the lovely treats and i can’t wait to try them! they also have fire coffees that you can add CBD to. check it out for sure!
Food is amazing, great coffee and atmosphere. Love the vegan breakfast options. Staff is the friendliest!

The space has a large amount of seating even though it is small, including multiple outdoor tables with umbrellas! Wine, baked goods, prepared foods, bottled drinks galore inside as well as an extensive menu with tons of vegan/veg options and homemade breads for sandwiches. Lower prices than most places. First time here and I got the veggie Cindy's breakfast, which came with hashbrowns, and was literally larger than my head! Also got a cookie. All the food was even better than expected! I dont eat out often but will come back here because this is exactly the kind of local business I want to support. Come and try it!!
This is my favorite hidden gem! They have the best breakfast Sammy’s! They are so kind and hard working, always good service. Order ahead if you can too :)

Got up this morning, looked for vegan breakfast in Charlotte and by my surprise, there was this lovely locally owned restaurant with lots of vegan options a few blocks away from me in Merry Oaks. I dined in and adored the quaint seating area, with local arts for sale and the self serve condiment counter. It had everything you would ever need. The service was excellent and friendly. They answered all my quesions easily. The vegan food was great. I had the Vegan AF and coffee. Affordable prices and tons of vegan desserts too! We bought some after we ate to go. After being in Charlotte and vegan for 18 yrs, it's awesome having restaurants like this to support.
Fresh food for everyone! It's a veggie eaters delight because you've got numerous options for breakfast and lunch. The wraps are ENORMOUS! Check out the sides and dessert case too!

New vegan resident of Charlotte NC here 👋🏽. My wife found this gem on our way to our new home and we loved it. Many options to choose from and clever names on the menu. The last 2 visits have been a good experience and we're definitely coming back!

This place is the best meal we had in Charlotte. Super chic, casual, cool atmosphere. Lots of delicious options and the GF bread is one of the better ones I’ve tried. Usually GF options are small but not here!! - enormous and tasty portions. Keep doing what y’all are doing, 10/10. Will come back again if ever in the area.
Very cool, very unique. Tucked away in plain sight. Tons of vegan options, friendly staff. Very clean and very tasty. Will definitely be back.
Great coffee and sandwiches!

Hands down this place sells THE BEST TACOS IN ALL OF CHARLOTTE!!!! Even being vegan they are better than any other taco place I've been to here in Charlotte. Split 7 of their tacos between my husband and I to try each one and they did not disappoint. All of them were completely loaded, not like places that sell 90% tortilla and barely any meat. These were packed with as much goodness as they could fill in each taco. I have found the only taco place in Charlotte that I will go. Thankyou for amazing tacos and the fact that they are vegan is such a plus.
Fantastic food! Great people!
Everything I've had here was good. The bacon egg and cheese,  the sausage egg and cheese and the best was the barbque sandwich which is a MUST TRY!!
Great food! Wide selection of drinks and interesting deli sandwiches and salads. The Cindy Turkey sandwich was super tasty!
Delicious food and the absolute best customer service. Lots of vegan options!

This place saw had a high score BUT 2 small sandwich one smoothie and juicev40.00
So not worth it. Floors dirty cracks in floor on wall just not clean will never go back
Maybe 3.1 no were near 4.0
While eating the Plaza Torta, I ascended beyond time and space. So good.

Very good vegan place!!

They have great vegan tortas and other sandwiches that include a lot.. from chickpeas to avocados to sometimes both!

They also offer vegan smoothies !!
Really kind staff, delicious cake pops & coffee!

We always have a fabulous experience here, and this week they took it up a notch.  I stopped at the lunch hour and explained that I was hosting some vegan friends for dinner - asked if the vegan BLT (so good!) would keep until evening?  They packaged 4 sandwiches for me - deconstructed so the ingredients wouldn't get sloppy before then.  Was so "extra mile" and just as delicious as ever!  Fans for life!
if youre close please stop by for your sake. great owner and staff. i love the smoothies and wine
Amazing place!!! Don’t order through DoorDash, go directly to the website to order pick up! DoorDash charges more than the deli’s actual prices!

My girlfriend bought me a vegan cake from here and when we went to pick it up we decided to have brunch. There were incredible vegan options (the best vegan breakfast we have had in CLT). Their ice lattes were incredible and you can get them with CBD. The service was phenomenal (the lady who helped us was the absolute best and super accommodating). The crew even sang me happy birthday and made my day so special. Overall, this is our new spot for brunch. This is a hidden gem. I definitely recommend whether you are vegan or not. They go above and beyond.

First time customer and happy to see so many vegan options available. We ordered more food than we could eat and it was all delicious. The location was so cute and the people were so sweet. I ordered a coconut cake for my boyfriend birthday and he loved it.
Nice food
Great coffee and delicious food options! Cindy is the best!
I went here for the first time to get my sister a vegan lunch, the staff. Was wonderful and recommended 2 delicious vegan meals. My sister loved it.
Amazing sandwiches amazing staff!! Everything was delicious!!
Great and friendly staff and had an amazing sandwich. Good place
Great local Coffee and sandwiches.

My girlfriend and I had La Jarocha Torta and a Buffalo Chix Sandwhich, both vegan. It was so delicious!! Honestly other places like common market are so overrated. Deli St. has delicious vegan food with so much flavor. They’re staff is awesome too. Never disappoints, thank you for the great food!!
That might've been the best sandwich I've had in my life. Try the outsider on the house bread and thank me later.

Pretty bad customer service! The owner is very rude and mean. I will not be back here. I was excited to try this place, but left with disappointment. They only care about the money not about their customers.

Worst Customer Service Ever! I went there today and it was my first time. The owner rushed through explaining the menu to my friend and I. We ordered, the food took a while to come out but that was ok. Not a huge deal. We spent $45+ on two smoothies and two sandwiches, happily! I received my smoothie, and it was pretty awful. I did not like the taste at all. It was unbearable. I kindly asked the owner (the woman who suggested the smoothie to me) if I could swap it out because it was not to my liking. She sarcastically smiled and told me no. It was so sarcastic I thought she was joking. I asked her if she was serious, she said yes. She said they are barely making any money. She said they used to do that, but they do not any more because they need to make money.  As a new customer trying to support this minority owned business, I was very confused! I looked all over the Deli to see where that policy had been posted and it was no where to be found. I suggested that she post that somewhere if that is a policy they stand behind. Had I known that, I would have ordered something that I was certain that I would have liked. All in all, I found the owner to go about the situation very rudely and I will not be returning or recommending anyone to this place. The food was pretty good, but if you are looking for quality customer service DO NOT GO HERE.
I love this place! They have healthy food options, great atmosphere and lovely people working here!
Wonderful little local spot with amazing vegan options! It's so refreshing to have a place that has so many choices for vegans. Love it!!
This place is great... high quality ingredients, and that makes all the difference.

Deli St has THE best sandwiches. So delicious and fresh. It’s light feeling food but also incredibly savory. My favorites are the Cindy’s Turkey sandwich (the pimento cheese is so delish) and the Commonwealth. Love this place!

Their vegan sandwiches and baked goods are so delicious. I special ordered a vegan coconut cake and it was more affordable than other cakes I've special ordered from other places and was the most delicious cake I've ever had. I can't wait for the next special occasion so i can order another one! My non-vegan family had no idea it was vegan and all raved about the cake.

Loads of vegan options for breakfast and lunch.  I order delivery all the time.  My favorites are
breakfast: Vegan AF (pictured)
Lunch: Vegan BLT

Please try them out,  it's worth it.

Vegan croissants!!!!
One of the best vegan breakfast spots in Charlotte. Option to customized your food if you want to eat healthy.

In Charlotte visiting family, this is one of the best restaurant stops we've had. We had the El Chigon, the Sweet Holy Mess, and Cindy's Vegan breakfast wrap. All came with hashbrowns and were filling so the price is good. They were delicious! The cappuccino was good as well. Can't wait to try the fresh cookies we got to go from the nice deli area inside. Staff was friendly and the atmosphere was relaxed with local art and lots of plants. Hope we can come back when we're in Charlotte next.
Love that they serve breakfast all day.

Disappointed I waited 10 min for a sandwich that was pretty basic to make and they got it wrong. Some how a turkey prov lettuce tomato mayo ended up being just literally turkey and prov on bread for 7 bucks.
Great service, amazing staff and SOOO MANY options. 😋
Ordered two vegan af's and paid 25 bucks for flat lifeless sandwiches that didn't have the hashbrowns...

Wow! We are so blessed to have such a wonderful deli and sandwich shop in our backyard in Plaza Midwood, on Central Avenue!. Service is out of this world, best sandwiches I’ve had in a long time! Vegan, gluten-free options as well. Great spot!
Incredibly fresh and delicious food! I have found my go-to for chicken salad. Online ordering from their website is seamless.

Love love love this place.  Every time I come to Charlotte, we come here for breakfast.  They have many vegan options as well as non vegan options.  It’s so good and I love the chill laid back atmosphere.  You can’t go wrong checking this little spot out.
Great place with lots of vegan options! The Vegan AF and El chingon are great.
Awesome neighborhood spot!!! Great food
I usually love this place but today I bought their dog cupcakes and when I got home I noticed there was mold on them. I'm glad I noticed before feeding it to my dog.
Delicious vegan and non-vegan menus with great pastries.

Friendly staff, wonderful owners and always delicious food!!
This place often saves my hungry life when I am on the go! Great vegan options...these are my 2 go to sandwiches. The Vegan BLT and the Beyond Wrap 🔥 Call in your order-pick it up in the drive-thru and leave the hard-working employees a good tip!!
Great vegan food. Good value. Love the sausage, tofu scramble and cheese sandwich.
Delicious but expensive
Great atmosphere and fantastic service. Delicious food and lots of drink options, the smoothies are a must.

Their food is great but it’s best to call your order in because apparently they cannot afford mistakes and will not remake your order if you make a mistake ordering online. I was told “times are weird” and they lose too much money remaking things. Understandable but not respectable considering this policy is no where in writing. Not to mention, I am a repeat customer. They are more concerned about saving money than customer satisfaction is what I take from this.

If you go here you have to try the avocado ciabatta, really good mix of flavors and the seasoning adds just the perfect touch.. they have all kinds of food options for those who are picky eaters. The self standing restaurant is conveniently located on Central Avenue and Logie; drive thru window is available along with some outdoor seating. A little bit pricey but definitely worth treating yourself once in awhile..
Good food. Good people. Deli St Charlotte.
Good sandwich.
Best brunch spot in CLT. Super friendly staff and so many vegetarian and vegan options

This place is absolutely amazing! I tried the torta sandwich with steak and cheese and it was delectable and spicy and so flavorful. I will definitely be back. They had amazing vegan options as well for my friend!!

FIVE STARS. my favorite deli in charlotte. amazing vegan and vegetarian options fill up half the menu, other half is non-vegetarian and equally delicious. price-wise, around the same price as most deli’s in charlotte, but much better taste and quality. customer service is great and the aesthetics are also very cool. definitely my go-to spot for nice vegetarian sandwiches.
Great place to eat. The Vegan options are great as well. The wraps are packed and neatly rolled, as well as the other food as well.

I am late in posting this, but my wife and I REALLY enjoyed this place.  The staff was friendly, and we were so thankful that they have a vegan menu!  The egg/cheese sandwich that I tried was rather tasty.  We will definitely be coming back.  Go vegan!  Go local!  Go Deli St.!
excellent service and great food
Excelente servicio y excelente comida
Exquisita toda la comida, un lugar agradable, tranquilo y con una excelente atención por parte de todo su personal. Nos hizo sentir en casa.
Good food. It's pretty expensive for the little amount that you get but the employees are cool and it's convenient.
Great atmosphere and selection!
Great food and customer service. Vegan, vegetarian, and non-vegetarian options available.

Stopped by for a sandwich on a Monday afternoon. Upon entering it's a little overwhelming, there are so many options for sandwiches, vegan and "regular"??, along with smoothies, drinks, chips and other snack goods. After reviewing the menu for a bit, went with the country club sandwich, and it arrived a few minutes later.  The staff is super friendly and helpful btw! The sandwich was pressed and tasty, with fresh ingredients, cheese and mustard with just the right amount of tang. I would definitely return for another, or perhaps to try a breakfast sandwich in the AM.

Absolutely love this place, their food, and the staff. True professionals every step of the way. Always welcoming. The food is always fresh and delicious. They have a variety of desserts as well. Also an extensive craft beer collection. So happy they are in the hood.
Great local deli with unique great tasting options. I would order ahead because it is not the quickest. Local art for sale inside with local food options. It's really good overall.
They make some pretty good coffee and breakfast Sammies

So glad I finally stopped in! Hungry for lunch or breakfast all day? This is a great place with fresh, tasty food, reasonably priced, and a great ambiance decorated with artists' work, including beautiful plants. Also a monthly artist market in the parking lot, 1st Saturday of the month. 9:00-3:00. Staff is friendly and welcoming. Try it soon. You may become a regular.
We love Deli Street! Cindy and her family and staff are so welcoming. The food is wonderful with many local and vegan options. Breakfast and lunch and bottle shop must!

Breakfast to lunch, Deli St. ALWAYS delivers. Their Tortas are insanely good. ToGo beer/chip/coffee selection is always of a great variety. Service is always pleasant. Outside seating to enjoy the day. Charlotte if you aren’t eating here... you’re missing out.
Muy recomendado!!!

Fantastic vegan options! El Chingón (vegan egg cheese & sausage on a croissant) is my go-to. The tropical smoothie is delish. Staff is lovely & I love how they're always supporting local artists and small businesses!

I am so happy this place exists. Everything about it is nourishing to my soul. From the beetroot smoothie and vegan breakfast sandwiches on croissants, to the overall vibe— impecable playlist and gorgeous plants scattered about, this place is truly incredible. The service was great and the atmosphere was super relaxed.. they even had the food network on (praise). Our sandwiches came super quickly and even came with hash browns! The chingón sandwich was delish and a comforting vegan version of breakfast sandwiches I ate as a kid. I love this place.
Excellent food and service at a great price!
We really enjoyed the tortas! The atmosphere here is also great, loved all the plants and artwork. Excited to try the other options on the menu, lots of vegan options
consistently great.
Awesome people, sandwiches, and coffee! Great healthy options and bodega style snacks and drinks. Not to mention a really cool drive thru!

I asked the owner if it was the same bacon and she stated that it was but had the cook make me a new one and make the bacon crispy but it was absolutely the same. I have always had a pleasant experience with Deli St. But I will no longer coming back, due to my distrust I have. I need to trust that the ingredients are all vegan, the company should provide the ingredients as well as no what type of veggie bacon is being used. To me that is unacceptable.

This is a great little sandwich shop! While on my last visit to Charlotte my friends I was visiting brought me here for lunch. What a great place! I knew the moment I walked in the door I was somewhere special.

The establishment was quite busy so we jumped in line and looked at the boards while waiting our turn. That turn came pretty quick and you could see the staff was a well oiled machine and handled the crowd like pros.

I ended up ordering the St Julian Club and switched the bread Sourdough. This comes loaded with Italian meats, provolone cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, roasted red peppers, oil, vinegar and oregano. It's basically an Italian club sandwich and frick'n delicious!!!

My friends ordered the Hawthorn Beef and the Country Club. The Hawthorn Beef came on Marbled Rye Bread which was loaded with roast beef, Swiss cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, habanero onions, pickles, spicy mustard and mayo. The Country Club was no slouch either and had roast beef, turkey, ham, cheddar and provolone cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, mayo and mustard.

What a super delicious lunch!  Frankly if I lived in Charlotte I'd be a regular here. No doubt about it. One other thing to point out is that this is also a store and you can get your own meats and baked goods from here all day long. They also have wines and smoothies, so there's something for everyone here. Check them out!
Friendly family run operation. Great breakfast sandwich with fresh ingredients and reasonable pricing. Will repeat.

reviews_data.review_text:
Vegan heaven it is. Soooo many options for ALL. It was our first time trying it and absolutely loved everything we ordered.
Their Vegan chocolate and carrot cake were amazing and so is Un Quickie and El Chingno(all vegan), excuse me if I’m spelling it wrong 😑 . Cute little cozy place and absolutely friendly staff. Must try.
I am a regular here for lunch, through original ownership and new. Hands down the best Torta in the city of Charlotte.

don’t let the unassuming exterior of the building fool you! deli st is fire! i got the st julien (italian) sub and it was absolutely fabulous. this cute lil’ deli carries a thoughtful assortment of accoutrements that includes a variety of vegan/veg/local offerings, wine and beer, the staff was super sweet, and the food was fresh and delicious. shop local!

Extremely disappointed in our visit today! We usually come here a few times a month and this time we were overcharged by quite a bit. The young lady stated their prices went up. Which I understand that prices increases but by $4 is ridiculous.  There are no prices on their menu and their online system states a total different price.

So it appears they are under new management and prices changed with new management as of the same day. This needs to be posted. This is extreme shady behavior and now they are blaming the clover system. Bad customer service!
Really good breakfast and lunch! Definitely worth the visit.

Looking for a breakfast that's both delicious and good for you?  Look no further than Deli St, a charming little spot that's quickly become my go-to for a healthy and satisfying morning meal.
From the moment you walk in, the bright and airy atmosphere sets the tone for a positive start to the day.  The décor is modern and clean, with pops of color and plenty of natural light.  It's a welcoming space, whether you're grabbing a quick bite on your way to work or settling in for a leisurely brunch with friends.
They offer a wide variety of options, catering to different dietary needs and preferences.  The staff is also incredibly friendly and knowledgeable, always happy to offer recommendations or answer questions about the menu.

Deli St. is a fantastic addition to the breakfast scene.  If you're looking for a healthy and delicious way to start your day, this is the place to be.  I highly recommend checking them out!  I give them a solid 5 out of 5 stars.
Cool place good coffee, friendly and helpful employee!
I love this place because it feels local and has great tasting food. Can be a bit pricey at times but it’s custom-made. Feels like a mom and pop deli from New York City.
Great vegan options.

reviews_data.review_text: We visited on a Friday afternoon for lunch.  I got the Cindy Turkey and Jo got the avocado chicken salad.  This is place is very friendly.  Service is quick and the food is good.  Definitely recommend this place.

They tell they can’t make my food bc they close their ktichen at 3:30 and I clearly have 15 minutes till they “close their kitchen” obviously they were lazy and did not want to work and get out of there. Won’t be giving my money to them anymore. Hopefully the owner/management can speak to their female employees about the hours of operations. Owner wasn’t present which is probably why the girls decided to make their own times up. Shame

Yum!! This place is great! I had The Plaza torta, my friend had a smoothie both were outstanding!! The ambiance is nice and parking easy!
Great little brunch spot. Small interior but cozy with cool interior design. Small patio with a few tables. Very vegan friendly but plenty of standard items.
The customer service is always so friendly and they have so many vegan options!! The brownie and chocolate cake are insanely good and they have a full breakfast and lunch menu too.
The food is amazing, it's rarely too crowded, and it has a hard time getting boring. Amazing place to let the hours fly by with or without food.
Always fresh, friendly and delish. I always pick up at the drive thru, but it looks nice from outside too. Wish this review would let me add a photo of my sandwich...

Deli St has become my go to place for breakfast, lunch, and tacos! Their menu is extensive and vegan choices are plentiful. I have never tried anything I didn’t like here. The place is super cozy and nice with local art and cool plants. Outdoor and indoor seating so that you can enjoy our beautiful Charlotte weather when possible (almost all the time). The staff is super attentive and nice. They have a wide variety of drink options and their pastries are to die for!

I don’t often leave reviews, but I have to for Deli St.

The staff members were so kind, the menu is extensive, and everything we ordered was amazing. There’s ample parking, a drive-thru, well-shaded outdoor seating, and tons of vegan options.

We don’t live in Charlotte anymore, but if we did, this would be our go-to breakfast, lunch, and pastry spot.

Deli St is absolutely amazing. They don’t skimp on anything and it’s healthy (if you want fresh veggies and vegan options). Their vegan beyond wrap is a great deal (it’s so giant, don’t ever change!). Love love love! ♥️♥️♥️

When I first discovered this place I was delighted... but that changed quickly when I went to call in an order and the call kept dropping (or so I thought...) Still wanting a nice vegan breakfast I decided to walk in and place the order myself. I was curious about the phone issue so I called while waiting in line. The guy working the register answered it promptly... ok so I was getting hung up on. Not sure why but ok I'm here now might as well order.

I ordered the hottie in the morning (a vegan dish) and requested just egg as an extra and the vegan bacon. They gave me an actual omelet (yes I can tell the difference) and ACTUAL BACON. I've been vegan for over 10 years now. Why they would do this I have no clue. I was specific in what I asked for with the add-ons so I'm not sure why I received meat and eggs with this dish. This place is NOT VEGAN FRIENDLY AT ALL!!! VEGANS BEWARE THIS IS YOUR WARNING!!!

As a vegetarian this is by far my favorite breakfast place in Charlotte. Great people, quaint little area, and incredible food. From their breakfast sandwiches with egg, cheese, hash brown, and vegan sausage on their house Bolilo or the vegan buffalo chix sandwich with house ranch, as well as the great smoothies and coffee....this place rocks.

Vegetarians/Vegans in Charlotte, NC who have not had a chance to step in and have a bite in the cozy atmosphere with the great owner/staff are missing out big-time!

Food so good it  will make you exchange a lambo in for a car battery. Food so good it will make you  stand in the DMV line for fun. Food so good you can stream  youtube videos on a pager. All jokes aside, Its always a pleasure coming there in the morning and feeling so grateful to have vegan breakfast options 7 days out of the week. Stopped in for first-time visit on 11/20/23. Entry way has books to take/exchange. Nice! Outdoor seating in front under umbrellas. Surprising selections of beers and ales, lots of baked goods, breakfast all day and a full vegan menu. Coffees and baked goods are reasonably priced. I got a 12 oz mocha latte and a huge blueberry muffin for $7. Both were excellent. BTW, they also have a surprising selection of wines from around the world. I picked up 2 bottles of nice Italian wine to take to the fam for Thanksgiving. Friendly staff, warm vibes. Come visit this place; it's a happy little surprise. 😊
I've been coming here every Sunday before my kickball games (about 2 months) and this place never disappoints. Great service and food and way better than Common Market
Good variety of vegetarian and vegan options, plus good coffee and bakery treats

Breakfast sandwiches are on another level. Came to Charlotte for a 4-day vacation and ate here twice for breakfast.

My only con is that the coffee is a tad too hot when served, but I'm busy eating the sandwich while it cools down.

Today I had the pleasure of having lunch at Deli St and OMG I had the vegan BLT and the vegan quesadillas(this will be dinner).  Everything was seasoned well, hot and so much!! Customer service excellent!!  Definitely will be trying the vegan menu more!!  Thank you

A few people had recommended Deli Street and we were anxious to check it out.

We went there last week and it was wonderful!!  I can see why they spoke so highly of the place.

Ample parking, a fun entry with cute plaques about coffee & a lending library, interesting artwork (some for sale), a menu with lots of choices, super clean, friendly staff, and good vibes.

They have a vegan menu and a non-vegan menu so there is something for everyone!

They are very dog-friendly and have a nice outdoor seating area.

Most importantly, the food is fantastic!! We got sandwiches and hash browns, and desserts to go.  The vegan BLT on house bread was out of this world and the coconut cake was delectable and decadent (and I got 3 portions out of it), as was a huge cookie with nuts on it.  All homemade.

They are in the happening Plaza Midwood neighborhood, easy to get to, and even have a drive through.

Highly recommend and we'll definitely be back.
Every Vegan menu item from Deli St is so amazing. I order from here alll the time. The vegan torta is so delis!
I got the steak sandwhich it is amazing. Customer service is great and the food comes out quick and tastes amazing.
AMAZING food, great coffee/ espresso… nice staff and a very chill vibe
Always fresh deli meat, really like going here

Great food, great coffee, and great staff! Visiting for the day and glad I chose this spot for my breakfast.

Really nice atmosphere, really amazing food, and options for literally everyone!!!
I will be back

It would be impossible for me to express how much I love Deli St but I’ll at least try!! Incredibly kind staff and owners, awesome beer selection, my favorite vegan breakfast in town (the hottie in the morning - add scrambled tofu), irresistible vegan baked goods, and more recently the best vegan tacos I’ve ever had in my life via their in-store pop up “Taco Vegano”. Deli St. is the absolute BEST place for coffee, breakfast, or lunch in Charlotte! Incredible vegan options, awesome people, A+ service, and stellar vibe!! Would give em 10 stars if I could!!!
The best local spot in CLT for lunch. The bow tie pasta salad is incredible. They also have great deserts and dog treats. Give them a chance and you’ll be back.

The cashier was nice and the place has a great variety of drinks. However, the food lacks seasoning and flavor. I ordered the El Chingón (vegan)and the  and the tofu was not really seasoned.

I also ordered the vegan Beyond wrap. It was a decent size, but it is was not seasoned well. I feel like there should have been a sauce added to it. And for $12.99 it should have also included a side. But, there was no side.

I will probably give this place another try once they get a better sanitation grade. It was a 90 when I ordered today.

A little different than my usual. Food was very good, prices not out of line, but it would be helpful to have prices on the menu. I don't like having to ask for prices. Very clean, limited seating. I strongly recommend this place for breakfast sandwiches or lunch. My party of 3 enjoyed our food and the experience. We have a new favorite.
Great place for tasty smoothies and sandwiches!!!!

I love the food and the people that works there, they have a lot of vegan options
Wonderful sandwiches and great service in a hip atmosphere. Definitely worth a visit!!

Deli St is a gem of the Plaza Midwood area. Great vegetarian and nonvegetarian options that are significantly better than any fast food you could get to-go. I tried the vegan club and would absolutely get it again.

Great place to eat with lots of vegan options! Very friendly staff and the owner is so sweet. Vegan breakfast options are the best! They also sell tacos on weekend evenings and WOW. The traditional tacos I've been craving for years. I could eat 40 of them. Cindy is so nice and always makes us feel like family.
